# Color Token System

## Single Source of Truth

All accent/CTA colors are defined as CSS custom properties in `apps/electron/src/renderer/styles/globals.css`:

| Variable | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `--mi-accent` | Primary accent (buttons, links, highlights) |
| `--mi-accent-rgb` | RGB triplet for use in `rgba()` |
| `--mi-accent-dark` | Darker shade (secondary charts, borders) |
| `--mi-accent-light` | Lighter shade (hover states, subtle text) |
| `--mi-accent-bg` | Low-opacity background tint |
| `--mi-accent-border` | Low-opacity border tint |

Tailwind maps these via `tailwind.config.js` → `accent.*`, `indigo.*`, `status.info`.

## Rules

1. **Never hardcode accent hex values** (`#82C0CC`, `#3A7A87`, etc.) in components.
   Use `var(--mi-accent)`, `var(--mi-accent-dark)`, etc. in inline styles,
   or Tailwind classes like `text-accent`, `bg-accent`, `border-accent`.
2. **For rgba with opacity**, use `rgba(var(--mi-accent-rgb), <opacity>)`.
3. **Fallback values** in `rgba(var(--mi-accent-rgb, 130,192,204), 0.2)` must match the current accent RGB. If the accent changes, update `globals.css` and these fallbacks will be stale — so prefer omitting fallbacks when possible.
4. **CSS files** that need the accent (e.g. `calendar-theme.css`) should reference `var(--mi-accent)`, not repeat the hex.
5. **Canvas 2D / SVG chart contexts** cannot resolve `var(--mi-accent)`. Use `getComputedStyle(document.documentElement).getPropertyValue('--mi-accent')` to resolve the hex at draw-time. See `getCssVar()` helper in `activityChart.ts` and `DashboardView/index.tsx`.
6. **Non-accent colors** (status green, rose, neutral grays) are fine as direct hex — they don't change with the brand accent.
